	<clause id="_mathematical_model_of_the_measurement" obligation="normative"><title>Mathematical model of the measurement</title><p id="_994a20e8-2da5-475f-9a9b-72a1c9e50cd6">The measurement equation for the radiometer signal, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>S</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></math></stem>, is the following <xref target="eq1"/>:</p>
	<formula id="eq1">
	<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>S</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>K</mi></mstyle><msubsup><mrow><mo>∫</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>∞</mo></mrow></msubsup><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>ɛ</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle><mi>,</mi><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><mi>s</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>L</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>b</mtext></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle><mi>,</mi><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><mtext>d</mtext><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle><mi>.</mi></math></stem>
	</formula>
	<p id="_b7dd1fae-2c23-421f-9f00-1a53b0de153b">The terms in the equation are: <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>K</mi></mstyle></math></stem> is a geometric factor associated with the actual form of primary radiometry, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>ɛ</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle><mi>,</mi><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></math></stem> the emissivity of the blackbody radiator, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>s</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></math></stem> the spectral responsivity, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>L</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>b</mtext></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle><mi>,</mi><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></math></stem> the Planck function and <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>T</mi></mstyle></math></stem> the thermodynamic temperature.</p>


